 South Africa has a total of 7 220 confirmed Covid-19 cases according to an announcement by the minister of health, Dr Zweli Mkhize, on Monday, May 4. A total of 53 of those cases have been recorded in Mpumalanga. According to data released by the Mpumalanga Department of Health, 22 recoveries have been recorded to date. There have been no deaths recorded in Mpumalanga. • Bushbuckridge: 1 case
